  "prompt": "What marks and rank is required to get Aerospace Engineering in IIT Bombay in JEE Advanced 2017?",
  "response": "To secure admission to the Aerospace Engineering program at IIT Bombay through JEE Advanced 2017, candidates needed to achieve a competitive rank. While specific cutoff marks vary each year based on the difficulty of the exam and the number of candidates, here are some general insights:\n\n### JEE Advanced 2017 Rank for Aerospace Engineering at IIT Bombay:\n- The closing rank for Aerospace Engineering at IIT Bombay in 2017 was typically around **300-400 (General Category)**. This rank could vary slightly depending on factors like reservation categories.\n\n### Marks Required:\n- JEE Advanced scores are normalized and reported as a percentage or percentile. To achieve a rank in the 300-400 range, candidates likely needed to score in the **top 0.1% - 0.2%** of test-takers. This roughly translates to scoring **250+ marks out of 360** (subject to normalization).\n\n### Factors Affecting Admission:\n1. **Category**: Cutoff ranks vary for General, OBC, SC, ST, and PwD categories.  \n2. **Yearly Competition**: The number of candidates and exam difficulty influence the cutoff ranks.  \n3. **Normalized Scores**: Marks are normalized across sessions to ensure fairness.\n\n### Advice:\nAspiring candidates should aim for a rank well within the top 500 (General Category) to have a strong chance of securing a seat in Aerospace Engineering at IIT Bombay. Focus on consistent preparation and solving previous years' papers for better insights into the exam pattern.",
